.TH "xemaclite_update_address" 9 "xemaclite_update_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xemaclite_update_address \- Update the MAC address in the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xemaclite_update_address
.BI "(struct net_local *drvdata "  ","
.BI "u8 *address_ptr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drvdata" 12
Pointer to the Emaclite device private data
.IP "address_ptr" 12
Pointer to the MAC address (MAC address is a 48-bit value)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tx must be idle and Rx should be idle for deterministic results.
It is recommended that this function should be called after the
initialization and before transmission of any packets from the device.
The MAC address can be programmed using any of the two transmit
buffers (if configured).
